    <h2><a id="shai" href="https://okcthunderwire.usatoday.com/2021/04/17/daigneault-provides-injury-update-on-shai-gilgeous-alexander/">Shai Gilgeous Alexander Return? Injury Updates?</a></h2>
<center>
 <a href="#"><img class="border" src="https://img.bleacherreport.net/img/images/photos/003/903/015/hi-res-123e08cc982ec7f1ebef687536b7ca67_crop_north.jpg?1613017999&w=3072&h=2048" width="1000" height="700"></a>
   
 <p>Oklahoma City Thunder point guard Shai Gilgeous ALexander has missed the past several games with a foot injury. He was expecteds to return this week back has been set back another 2 weeks after an evaluation. Shai has had an outstanding 3rd year averaging 22 points per game. The Thunder have struggled without him going 4 and 6 in their last 10 games. Coach Daigneault stated:“He’s definitely progressed, but not to the point we would have liked,” Daigneault said. “He’s probably a little bit behind what we were looking for.” Do the Thunder still have a chance to make the playoffs with the return of Shai? They are currently thet 11 seed in the westsern conference and sit 6 games behind playoff contention. They will have to make a pushto make it and maybe with the return of Shai, it is possible.  </p>
