    <h2><a id="second" class="border" href="https://www.nba.com/news/power-rankings-2020-21-week-18">Latest NBA Power Rankings: Sixers Retake Number 1 Over Clippers</a></h2>
<center>
<a href="#"><img class="border" src="https://a.espncdn.com/photo/2021/0418/nba_power_rankings_1296x729.jpg"></a>

    <p> As the NBA season is nearing towards the end, many teams have began hot streaks and have been playing some of their best basketball of the season. The 1 seed Sixers have stayed consistent over the course of the season and have proved they are serious title contenders after a dissapointing early exit last season. The Clippers fall to the 2nd seed as they have continued to play well, but Sixers have been on a whole new level. The susn have also fell to the the 3rd seed. A big story is last years champions, the Lakers, who have fallen all the way to the 9 seed as they continue to struggle without Lebron James or Anthony Davis. They are hoping just to stay in the playoff picture ao their 2 best players can come back well rested and ready for playoff time as they seek to become back to back champions.</p>
